goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight delays and the range of delay times.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between flight distance and delay time?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of distance vs delay
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or trends between flight distance and delay time.

goals.question: What is the average flight time?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of flight times and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight distances and the range of distance values.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight time and delay time?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of time vs delay
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or trends between flight time and delay time.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between flight distance and delay time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['time'])
    avg_time = data['time'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_time, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Time: {avg_time:.2f} hours')
    plt.title('What is the average flight time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Hours')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
